The paper focuses on object detection using a foveated visual system, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the computational and metabolic cost savings of using a foveated visual system, which could fall under the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of foveation on bottom-up saliency, which could relate to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
